<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="17">
Comments. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182908" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Adelomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Adelomyrmex costatus Fernández" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costatus">A. costatus</taxonomicName>
has a continuous mesosoma, the promesonotum is conspicuously and evenly convex, the petiolar node is thick, and there is coarse longitudinal costulation. This combination of characters is unique in the genus.
</paragraph>
